      • setM

        public Word setM(Word newWord)
        Mutable sets this object with the given object. This is added to make changes in the passed parameters. For example, if we want to change the value of argument A in func(Word A) with the word B, then if you make a statement like "A = B;" inside the method, it does not affect A. But with this method, we can affect the argument.
        Parameters:
        newWord - the new value of this object
        Returns:
        this object
